The paper deals with the application of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for face anti-spoofing, which involves detecting spoofed faces in biometric-based access control systems. This falls under the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category, which deals with the analysis and processing of visual data. Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques such as CNNs, which falls under the Machine Learning (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper also deals with the security aspect of biometric-based access control systems, which falls under the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance evaluation of different CNN architectures, which falls under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the application of CNNs for a specific task, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
